# NEMETIC STRING
# Moral_Frameworks_Emotional_Boundaries (C188)

Φ(Moral_Frameworks) = σ(unity|division) ∘ ρ(empathy|limitation) ∘ λ(certainty|curiosity) ∘ β(cohesion|constraint) ∘ δγ(grounding|rigidity) ∘ μ(structure|flexibility) + ε | :tensional

# OPERATOR BREAKDOWN
# σ(unity|division)          :: Air  :: Moral systems create collective unity while dividing in-group from out-group
# ρ(empathy|limitation)      :: Water :: Emotional boundaries channel empathy while limiting its flow
# λ(certainty|curiosity)     :: Fire  :: Moral conviction provides energy yet burns away openness
# β(cohesion|constraint)     :: Wood  :: Shared values grow community bonds that can constrain branching
# δγ(grounding|rigidity)     :: Earth :: Moral foundations ground identity but can harden into inflexibility
# μ(structure|flexibility)   :: Metal :: Ethical frameworks provide structure that may become too rigid
